 As the famous David Tepper, a hedge fund legend, noted, highest returns are made through a mix of both technical as well as fundamental analysis. But as our analysis says, this is not evidently with this stock.
Hedge Funds Ownership
 As of Q2 2015, 34 institutional investors have shares in Eastern Co. In Q2 2015, this company had 35.64% institutional ownership. That is a low interest. They decreased by 463,290 the total shares they hold. As of that quarter these asset managers owned 2.23 million shares. There were 5 funds that closed their positions and 10 that reduced them. A total of 3 funds opened new positions in Eastern Co and 10 increased their holdings.

 Minerva Advisors Llc had the greatest investment with ownership of 371,774 shares as of Q2 2015 for 4.19% of the fund’s portfolio. Warren Lichtenstein’s Steel Partners Holdings L.P. is another positive investment manager owning 23,248 shares of the company or 0.08% of their stocks portfolio. The Connecticut-based fund Retirement Design & Management Inc Adv have 0.19% of their stock portfolio invested in the company for 11,796 shares. Further, North Star Investment Management Corp. disclosed it had purchased a stake worth 0.40% of the fund’s stock portfolio in the company. Deprince Race & Zollo Inc was also a big believer in the Connecticut-based company, owning 160,591 shares. Eastern Co is 0.04% of the fund’s stock portfolio.
Eastern Co NASDAQ:EML Company Profile
The Eastern Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial hardware, security products and metal products from six the United States operations and seven wholly owned foreign subsidiaries. The Company maintains thirteen physical locations. The Company operates in three business segments: Industrial Hardware, Security Products and Metal Products. The Security Products segment provides products that safeguard property and control access. The Industrial Hardware segment manufactures a selection of latches, locks and other security hardware used in the transportation and industrial sector. The Company’s Metal Products segment manufactures anchoring devices for supporting underground mine roofs. The Company operates from locations in the United States, Canada, Mexico, Hong Kong, Taiwan and China.
Company Website: Eastern Co
 Eastern Co was founded in Connecticut on 1912-10-14. The firm has 942 employees. At the moment its market value is: $101.98 million and it has 6.37 million outstanding shares. Currently the company has 42.99% shareholders and the institutional ownership stands at 42.99%. The stock closed at $16 yesterday and it had average 2 days volume of 1056 shares. It is down from the 30 days average shares volume of 2805. Eastern Co has a 250 days low of $15.38 and a 52w high of $20.65. The current price is below the 200 days simple moving average.
