Executive Profile
James Anthony Mitarotonda  Co-Founder, Principal, President, Chief Executive Officer, and Chairman, Barington Capital Group, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 17 different industries.See Board Relationships63--
Background

		Mr. James Anthony Mitarotonda, also known as Jim, co-founded Barington Capital Group LP in November 1991 and serves as its Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, President and Principal. Mr. Mitarotonda serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer at Barington Companies Investors LLC. He has extensive public company director experience; financial, investment banking and corporate governance expertise and experience investing in industrial and specialty chemical companies. ... Mr. Mitarotonda served as Chief Executive Officer at Barington/Hilco Acquisition Corp. from July 24, 2014 until May 1, 2015. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Costar Technologies, Inc. from January 1, 2004 to December 17, 2004 and its President from May 16, 2006 to December 17, 2004. Mr. Mitarotonda served as Co-Chief Executive Officer at L Q Corporation, Inc. from April 2003 to October 2004 and served as its Chairman from April 2003 to October 2006. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer at George Foreman Enterprises Inc. from January 18, 2001 to May 19, 2004. He was an Investment Banking Professional of Citigroup Inc. He co-founded Commonwealth Associates in May 1988. He served as Co-Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at JMJ Management Company Inc. From December 1984 to May 1988, he served as a Senior Vice President of Investments at DH Blair & Co. Inc. He was employed at Citibank, N.A. in an executive capacity having management responsibility for two of Citibank's business banking branches where he served as the Regional Director of Citibank's home equity financing and credit services. Mr. Mitarotonda has been Chairman of the Board of The Eastern Company since January 1, 2016. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Prodos Capital Management LLC. He serves as Chairman of Business Advisory Board at Queens College. He served as the Chairman of Barington/Hilco Acquisition Corp. from July 24, 2014 to May 16, 2017 and its Director since July 24, 2014. He has been Independent Director of A. Schulman, Inc. since October 2005. He has been a Director of Kiddie Academy International, Inc. since January 1996; Nine West Holdings, Inc. since June 14, 2013; Pep Boys - Manny, Moe & Jack since August 3, 2006 and The Eastern Company since May 20, 2015. He has been an Independent Director of OMNOVA Solutions Inc. since March 19, 2015. Mr. Mitarotonda serves as a Director of United Services Management Corporation. He serves as a Director of Xenometrix Inc., Akron and is a Member of the Alumni Advisory Council of New York University's Stern School of Business. He is a Director of The Friends of Green Chimneys. He served as the Chairman of Pep Boys - Manny, Moe & Jack from July 2008 to June 2009. Mr. Mitarotonda served as a Director of Ebix, Inc. from January, 2015 to March 25, 2015. He served as a Director of Griffon Corporation from November 2007 to January 31, 2012. He served as a Director of Ameron International Corporation since March 30, 2011. He served as a Director of Costar Technologies, Inc. since September 11, 2003. He served as a Director of Register.com, Inc. since July 2003. He served as a Director of George Foreman Enterprises Inc. until May 19, 2004. He served as a Director of Sielox, Inc. He served as a Director of Gerber Scientific, Inc. since June 2010. He served as a Director at L Q Corporation, Inc. from September 2002 to October 2006. He served as a Director of The Jones Group Inc. since June 14, 2013. Mr. Mitarotonda was a Co-Chairman of Membership of the Gotham Chapter of the Young President's Organization. He holds an M.B.A. from New York University's Graduate School of Business Administration (now known as the Stern School of Business) and graduated from Queens College with a B.A. degree in Economics.Read Full Background




